snippet.textDisplay: Separation isn’t divorce and it shouldn’t be thought of as an end to marriage. Seperation is when two people give each other space and have time to reflect on things and focus on themselves for a while. I understand you and Amna have given each other space and time but sometimes you need to be given space and time through seperating and then if you come back and things still aren’t settling for a while, that’s when you should think about divorce, because just as you said marriage isn’t a joke especially if u have a kid involved. Also, time apart from your partner could make you appreciate them more and realise the importance of them in your life, which will make you reluctant to argue about petty things with them and more willing to compromise.
